comments: Carter (MIL) takes a step toward Pokusevski (OKC), causing marginal contact to occur, which he is able to move through.
Allen (MIL) has a resting hand on Giddey's (OKC) body as Giddey elevates for the rebound and secures it. The contact is marginal.
Mann (OKC) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it from Carter (MIL) as he receives the inbound pass.
Allen (MIL) maintains verticality and absorbs the contact that occurs during Mann's (OKC) layup attempt.

As Mann (OKC) jumps toward the basket during his shot attempt, marginal contact occurs with Allen (MIL). Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Carter (MIL) makes incidental hand-on-ball contact with Dort (OKC) during his layup attempt.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) and Matthews (MIL) both engage and separate as they vie for the loose ball.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) releases away from Carter (MIL) as he changes directions at the end of his drive.
After communicating with the Replay Center, it was determined that the ball did not make contact with the rim, and play resumed with OKC ball and 2.6 on the shot clock.
Pokusevski (OKC) establishes himself in Matthews' (MIL) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Pokusevski (OKC) moves alongside Lopez's (MIL) path and maintains verticality as he absorbs the contact on the driving shot attempt.
Carter (MIL) does not overtly or abruptly extend his leg out as incidental contact occurs with Dort (OKC) during the jump shot attempt.
Lopez (MIL) is firming up over his right foot during the pick to Dort (OKC), and marginal contact occurs as the pick is concluding.
Carter (MIL) swipes down and initiates contact with Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) wrist, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Dort (OKC) and Carter (MIL) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Williams (OKC) initiates contact as he goes to and through Carter (MIL) and dislodges him from his position as the screen is set.
Williams (OKC) goes to, not through, Matthews' (MIL) space and marginal contact occurs as the two come together during the screen. Matthews' reaction is not consistent with the level of contact.
Allen (MIL) moves laterally into Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) path, affecting his SQBR on his drive.
Allen (MIL) initiates contact with Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Pokusevski (OKC) makes marginal contact with Lopez's (MIL) off-arm after he has taken it off the ball during his shooting motion.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) brings his off-arm toward Matthews (MIL) and marginal contact occurs as Gilgeous-Alexander releases away without applying any force at the end of his drive.
Dort (OKC) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Pokusevski's (OKC) left arm cleanly dislodges the ball from Lopez (MIL) prior to incidental contact occurring on the driving shot attempt.
Mann (OKC) slides his hand off Portis' (MIL) off-arm during his layup attempt, and the contact is marginal.
Matthews (MIL) legally contests Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) jump shot attempt.
Dort (OKC) extends his lower body into Lopez (MIL) as he is airborne, affecting his body's trajectory on the layup attempt.

As Lopez (MIL) is moving toward the potential rebound, marginal contact occurs with Pokusevski (OKC). Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Matthews (MIL) and Dort (OKC) come together in pursuit of the loose ball and marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) legally contests Portis' (MIL) jump shot attempt.
Dort (OKC) is last to make contact with the ball before it goes out of bounds.

Replay review of the foul called on Hill (MIL) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Hill moves laterally into Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) path to initiate the contact during the drive. However, the basket did not count because Gilgeous-Alexander lands prior to his release on the shot attempt.
Dort (OKC) has an extended hand on Allen's (MIL) back, which dislodges him as he receives the inbound pass.
Giddey (OKC) commits a take foul on Allen (MIL).
After communicating with the Replay Center, it was confirmed that the offensive foul occurred prior to the release of the shot. MIL is awarded possession with 12.2 on the game clock.
Muscala (OKC) does not give Allen (MIL) time and space to avoid the contact during the screen.
Lopez (MIL) establishes himself in Dort's (OKC) path when marginal contact occurs as they come together. Dort's reaction is not commensurate with the level of contact.
As Pokusevski (OKC) and Allen (MIL) come together during the inbound, marginal contact occurs, which does not affect Allen's FOM.
Allen (MIL) goes to, not through, Pokusevski's (OKC) space and marginal contact occurs as the two come together off-ball.
Williams (OKC) commits a take foul on Allen.
Allen (MIL) initiates contact as he moves laterally into Giddey's (OKC) body, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Pokusevski (OKC) avoids making contact with Matthews (MIL) as they pursue the rebound.
Matthews (MIL) is last to make contact with ball before it goes out of bounds.
